JOHANNESBURG – The US military said it has carried out an airstrike in northern Somalia that killed 27 al-Shabaab extremists, AP reported. READ: Al Shabaab fighters seize town in central Somalia: residents The statement issued Monday by the US Africa command said it assessed that no civilians were killed in the attack on Sunday south-west of Bosasso, the commercial capital of the semi-autonomous Puntland state. The area has recently seen attacks on local forces by extremists aligned with the Islamic State group. African News Agency